+        // Here we wish to compute d = 2^(64+shift+1)/(m+2^64).
+        // Notice (m + 2^64) is a 65 bit number. This gets hairy. See
+        // libdivide_u32_recover for more on what we do here.
+        // TODO: do something better than 128 bit math
+
